Lúrio offers degree programs in 21 disciplines, enrolling 1,430 total students, including both undergraduate and postgraduate students. By 2013, the university had 192 professors and 1,430 students. As of 2008, the university had 43 faculty, of which 46.5% were women, and a student-to-faculty ratio of 17:1. The university is aiming to reach 80% of its faculty having a master's degree or higher, and its ideal is to have 70% of the faculty with master's degrees and 30% with doctorates.
